    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="31"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d31">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/717a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to President
                            <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 13, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: Sir Cecil<note n="32"
                        xml:id="d31fn1">Sir Cecil Spring Rice, the British Ambassador.</note> came
                    to see me Saturday evening and handed me the enclosed appeal by the Pope to the
                    belligerents which he said would soon be issued.<note n="33" xml:id="d31fn2">For
                        text of the Pope’s appeal, see <ref target="frus1917Supp02v01#pg_161">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1917, supp. 2, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 161</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>My own impression is that this statement of peace terms emanates from
                    Austria-Hungary and is probably sanctioned by the German Government. It is
                    undoubtedly preliminary to the Stockholm Conference.</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
